com.digi.xbee.api.packet.thread

Class TXIPv6Packet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.digi.xbee.api.packet.XBeePacket
      • com.digi.xbee.api.packet.XBeeAPIPacket
        • com.digi.xbee.api.packet.thread.TXIPv6Packet

  • public class TXIPv6Packet
extends XBeeAPIPacket
    This class represents a TX (Transmit) IPv6 packet. Packet is built using the parameters of the constructor or providing a valid API payload.
    Since:
    1.2.1
    See Also:
    RXIPv6Packet, XBeeAPIPacket

    • Constructor Detail

      • TXIPv6Packet

        public TXIPv6Packet(int frameID,
                    Inet6Address destAddress,
                    int destPort,
                    int sourcePort,
                    IPProtocol protocol,
                    byte[] data)
        Class constructor. Instantiates a new TXIPv6Packet object with the given parameters.
        Parameters:
        frameID - Frame ID.
        destAddress - IPv6 address of the destination device.
        destPort - Destination port number.
        sourcePort - Source port number.
        protocol - Protocol used for transmitted data.
        data - Transmit data bytes.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if frameID < 0 or if frameID > 255 or if destPort < 0 or if destPort > 65535 or if sourcePort < 0 or if sourcePort > 65535.
        NullPointerException - if destAddress == null or if protocol == null.
        See Also:
        IPProtocol, Inet6Address

    • Method Detail

      • createPacket

        public static TXIPv6Packet createPacket(byte[] payload)
        Creates a new TXIPv6Packet object from the given payload.
        Parameters:
        payload - The API frame payload. It must start with the frame type corresponding to a TX IPv6 packet (0x1A). The byte array must be in OperatingMode.API mode.
        Returns:
        Parsed TX IPv6 packet.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if payload[0] != APIFrameType.TX_IPV6.getValue() or if payload.length < .
        NullPointerException - if payload == null.
